title: Windows Java 11 native build failures after Smallrye JWT bump to 3.6.0
body:
### Describe the bug

Once https://github.com/quarkusio/quarkus/pull/30057 got merge, our [Beefy Scenarios](https://github.com/quarkus-qe/beefy-scenarios) daily build fails in native mode. Related to EdDsa by Jose4j.

Full logs here https://github.com/quarkus-qe/beefy-scenarios/actions/workflows/daily.yaml

### Expected behavior

Native build succeeds.

### Actual behavior

Native build fails with following exception message:

### How to Reproduce?

Reproducer:

Steps to reproduce the behavior:

0. make sure you use Windows
1. `git clone https://github.com/quarkus-qe/beefy-scenarios.git`
2. `mvn clean verify -Dnative -Dquarkus.native.native-image-xmx=6g -pl '003-quarkus-many-extensions'`

### Output of `uname -a` or `ver`

Microsoft Windows Server 2022

### Output of `java -version`

Java version: 11.0.17

### GraalVM version (if different from Java)

GraalVM Community, runtime: C:\hostedtoolcache\windows\graalvm-ce-java11-windows\22.3.0\x64\graalvm-ce-java11-22.3.0

### Quarkus version or git rev

999-SNAPSHOT

### Build tool (ie. output of `mvnw --version` or `gradlew --version`)

Apache Maven 3.8.6 (84538c9988a25aec085021c365c560670ad80f63)

### Additional information

_No response_
